vocabulary.json is built from two sources:

1. JLPT word lists by Jonathan Waller
   https://www.tanos.co.uk/jlpt/
   Used with permission. Lists cover vocabulary for JLPT levels N5–N1.

2. JMdict by the Electronic Dictionary Research and Development Group (EDRDG)
   https://www.edrdg.org/
   Licensed under Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported (CC BY-SA 3.0).
   https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/

Adaptations made in this project:
- Words matched against JMdict entries by kana/kanji reading
- Fields extracted: kana, kanji, romaji, meanings (with English and Swedish glosses),
  part of speech, register tags, antonyms, usage notes, JLPT level, frequency rank
- Romaji generated using pykakasi

This file and any derivative works incorporating the JMdict data must be distributed
under the same CC BY-SA 3.0 license.
